-$1.90 EPS Expected for Ascent Capital Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ASCMA) This Quarter


					Posted by Joanna Charbonneau on Jul 25th, 2017 // No Comments




Equities analysts expect Ascent Capital Group, Inc. (NASDAQ:ASCMA) to post earnings per share of ($1.90) for the current fiscal quarter, according to Zacks Investment Research. Two analysts have provided estimates for Ascent Capital Group’s earnings, with the highest EPS estimate coming in at ($1.82) and the lowest estimate coming in at ($2.04). Ascent Capital Group posted earnings of ($1.80) per share during the same quarter last year, which would indicate a negative year-over-year growth rate of 5.6%. The firm is expected to report its next quarterly earnings results  on Tuesday, August 8th.
According to Zacks, analysts expect that Ascent Capital Group will report full year earnings of ($7.24) per share for the current fiscal year, with EPS estimates ranging from ($7.44) to ($6.96). For the next year, analysts expect that the company will report earnings of ($7.26) per share, with EPS estimates ranging from ($8.42) to ($5.84). Zacks’ EPS averages are a mean average based on a survey of sell-side research firms that follow Ascent Capital Group.


 Get Ascent Capital Group Inc. alerts:



Ascent Capital Group (NASDAQ:ASCMA) last announced its earnings results on Tuesday, May 9th. The industrial products company reported ($1.56) earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, topping the consensus estimate of ($1.61) by $0.05. Ascent Capital Group had a negative net margin of 15.29% and a negative return on equity of 33.84%. The company had revenue of $141.20 million during the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $142.20 million. 





A number of research firms recently commented on ASCMA. Zacks Investment Research cut shares of Ascent Capital Group from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research note on Friday, May 12th. Imperial Capital dropped their price target on shares of Ascent Capital Group from $21.00 to $15.00 and set an “outperform” rating for the company in a research note on Thursday, May 11th.
Shares of Ascent Capital Group (NASDAQ:ASCMA) traded up 1.23% on Tuesday, reaching $17.33. 30,135 shares of the company traded hands. Ascent Capital Group has a 1-year low of $11.55 and a 1-year high of $26.16. The stock has a 50-day moving average price of $15.50 and a 200 day moving average price of $14.95. The firm’s market capitalization is $210.28 million. 
In related news, major shareholder Okumus Fund Management Ltd. sold 2,000 shares of Ascent Capital Group stock in a transaction dated Monday, July 17th. The shares were sold at an average price of $17.11, for a total transaction of $34,220.00. The sale was disclosed in a document filed with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through this hyperlink. Also, major shareholder Opportunistic Value Fun Okumus sold 150,000 shares of Ascent Capital Group stock in a transaction dated Thursday, July 20th. The shares were sold at an average price of $17.00, for a total transaction of $2,550,000.00. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. Over the last ninety days, insiders have sold 158,600 shares of company stock valued at $2,697,278. 8.65% of the stock is owned by corporate insiders. 
Several large investors have recently bought and sold shares of the stock. SG Americas Securities LLC acquired a new stake in  Ascent Capital Group during the first quarter valued at approximately $123,000.  First Manhattan Co. raised its stake in  Ascent Capital Group by 14.5% in the first quarter. First Manhattan Co. now owns 14,566 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $337,000 after buying an additional 1,842 shares in the last quarter.  First Quadrant L P CA acquired a new stake in  Ascent Capital Group during the second quarter valued at approximately $270,000.  Nine Chapters Capital Management LLC raised its stake in  Ascent Capital Group by 56.2% in the first quarter. Nine Chapters Capital Management LLC now owns 18,900 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $267,000 after buying an additional 6,800 shares in the last quarter.  Finally, Teachers Advisors LLC raised its stake in  Ascent Capital Group by 21.7% in the fourth quarter. Teachers Advisors LLC now owns 21,381 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $348,000 after buying an additional 3,808 shares in the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  82.58% of the company’s stock. 
